(1866, 1, '2016-08-13 09:53:27', '2016-08-13 09:53:27', 'Rajkumar Lamichhane is a singer and lyricist by profession. AKathmandu resident currently living in the Tokyo, Japan, Rajkumaris a very active social philanthropist to help back underprivilegedpeople in Nepal. Hes works as an executive in a company inTokyo but makes himself available to join the stage shows andthe local events to raise money for the kids of Nepal. Hefrequently travels back to home after gathering resources. Herecently provided scholarships to 50 needy students of Baglungdistrict with the resources he raised in Japan. Rajkumar has beenleading Sadbhaws Japan chapter since 2015.', 'Rajkumar Lamichhane', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'teadas', '', '', '2016-09-03 16:05:56', '2016-09-03 16:05:56', '', 0, 'http://localhost/sadbhaw/?post_type=leader&#038;p=1866', 0, 'leader', '', 0),
(1867, 1, '2016-08-13 09:53:45', '2016-08-13 09:53:45', 'My name is Yangkee Ghale is originally from Kathmandu, Nepal. She is a nursing student currentlyresiding in the Boston, United States. Yangkee strongly believes in being compassionate and helpingmankind selflessly in any way possible. So, she wanted to start it with her own native land, Nepal bybeing a part of an impactful and beautiful cause Sadbhaw Scholarship that aims to help provideeducation to the needy and deserving Nepali brothers and sisters where education isn''t given the firstpriority due to poor economic conditions. On behalf of our Nepali brothers and sisters and for the sakeof humanity, she requests everyone to help make a positive difference by helping the team of SadbhawScholarship in any way possible. Let''s take a common goal of providing equal educational opportunitiesto those in need and making a difference.', 'Yangkee Ghale', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'asdasdasdasd', '', '', '2016-09-03 16:05:27', '2016-09-03 16:05:27', '', 0, 'http://localhost/sadbhaw/?post_type=leader&#038;p=1867', 0, 'leader', '', 0),
(1868, 1, '2016-08-13 09:54:06', '2016-08-13 09:54:06', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sarala Thapa is the UK lead for Sadbhaw Schoalrships. Sarala believes making a difference starts with an individual''s willingness to help. As a UK chapter she hopes to raise awareness and extend this cause to gather help from more probable contributors for many more kids in Nepal. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Visiting different parts of Nepal and meeting people from different walks of life has been very eye opening for her. She believes education is the most important tool to help a child meet their full potential. Unfortunately, many young children are unable to attend school in Nepal. Sarala has a firm believe of making a difference starts with an individual''s willingness to help. After learning about Sadbhaw from a good friend, she also wanted make my small contribution. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sarala is currently sponsoring Nani Maya Lho from Makwanpur. It gives her immense happiness to know little contribution is helping a child receive the education she deserves. She hopes to commit to sponsor more children in the future.</span>', 'Sarala Thapa', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'asdasdasd-adas', '', '', '2016-11-08 05:22:49', '2016-11-08 05:22:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost/sadbhaw/?post_type=leader&#038;p=1868', 0, 'leader', '', 0),
